Rewrite in Python (#11)

The test agent has been rewritten in Python for several reasons

- More accessible to contributions. Python is basically pseudocode.
- Start up cost. The startup cost of the JVM was too heavy which was not practical for CI environments.
- Portability. While still not as portable as a binary, a Python interpreter is usually available or easy to acquire on developer and CI systems.

Along the way a new system has been put in place to do arbitrary checks which can/will be extended to support testing various properties about APM data.

Fix matching algorithm

The previous matching algorithm assumed that trace ids would be unique
across both sets of traces which is not true for snapshots as the traces
are normalized.

The matching is now done by sorting all the scores and then matching
based off the best score between traces.

feat: Add ddapm-test-agent-fmt command (#45)

New command that can be used to reformat snapshot
files to ensure a consistent style.

You can also use the command to check/error if files
are not conforming to the expected format.

$ ddapm-test-agent-fmt -h
usage: ddapm-test-agent-fmt [-h] [-v] [-c] [--log-level LOG_LEVEL] FILE [FILE ...]

Datadog APM Test Agent Snapshot Formatter

positional arguments:
  FILE                  Specific snapshot files or directories to format.

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -v, --version         Print version info and exit.
  -c, --check           Do not rewrite files, error if any files would be changed.
  --log-level LOG_LEVEL
                        Set the log level. DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR, CRITICAL.

test agent:

```
cnb@my-app:/var/run/datadog$ ls -la
total 4
drwxr-xr-x 2 root root   60 Aug  1 21:24 .
drwxr-xr-x 1 root root 4096 Aug  1 21:24 ..
srwxr-xr-x 1 root root    0 Aug  1 21:24 apm.socket
```

real agent:

```
cnb@my-app:/var/run/datadog$ ls -la
total 4
drwxr-xr-x 2 root root   80 Aug  1 21:30 .
drwxr-xr-x 1 root root 4096 Aug  1 21:31 ..
srwx-w--w- 1 root root    0 Aug  1 21:30 apm.socket
```

aiohttp doesn't seem to have a configurable way
to set these permissions but it does let us create and
manage a socket ourselves, so let's try that.

Fix race condition for simultaneous reading and writing (#101)

As discovered in https://github.com/DataDog/system-tests/pull/607,
concurrent requests to the test agent that read and write the data (like
sending and retrieving traces) could result in:

```
  File "/usr/local/lib/python3.9/site-packages/ddapm_test_agent/agent.py", line 184, in _traces_from_request
    return await self._decode_v04_traces(req)
  File "/usr/local/lib/python3.9/site-packages/ddapm_test_agent/agent.py", line 238, in _decode_v04_traces
    raw_data = await request.read()
  File "/usr/local/lib/python3.9/site-packages/aiohttp/web_request.py", line 649, in read
    chunk = await self._payload.readany()
  File "/usr/local/lib/python3.9/site-packages/aiohttp/streams.py", line 397, in readany
    await self._wait("readany")
  File "/usr/local/lib/python3.9/site-packages/aiohttp/streams.py", line 295, in _wait
    raise RuntimeError(
RuntimeError: readany() called while another coroutine is already waiting for incoming data
```
(https://github.com/DataDog/system-tests/actions/runs/3341145276/jobs/5532056812)

This was due to multiple `read()` calls being made on the request
object.

The solution is to fetch the data once off of the request object and
then store it on the object. Helpers are added to store requests and
retrieve the request data when necessary.

Change trace header handling (#121)

* Change headers to use received trace's content-type instead of relying on AioHTTP generated content-type

* Update headers to accept an optional argument of `X-Datadog-Agent-Proxy-Disabled` that disables trace proxying even if an agent URL is set. Also adds another optional argument of `X-Datadog-Proxy-Port` that can be included to update the agent URL on a trace-level basis.

feat: add optional more lenient trace decoder (#122)

This change adds the ability to configure a more lenient trace decoder. The advantage of this decoder is that any floats/ints within the meta field will be left as strings. Additionally, long integers that were originally being decoded to a string are now decoded correctly as integers. To enable the optional tracer, set the DD_DISABLE_TRACE_PARSE_ERRORS or --disable-trace-parse-errors runtime flag with a value of True.


Co-authored-by: Kyle Verhoog <kyle@verhoog.ca>

Add `SNAPSHOT_REMOVED_ATTRS` to remove attributes from spans in snapshots (#125)

Add a new optional configuration to allow fields to be removed from the spans. By default, no keys will be removed from the snapshots.

ðŸ’­ The motivation behind this feature is to get rid of some fields that can be noisy in the snapshots (e.g., start or duration) which could create some massive diffs when regenerating the snapshots.

Note that since the removal of the field start would cause an error when sorting the spans by this field, span_id was used as a fallback. Feel free to tell me if this would cause an issue I didn't consider (this is the reason why both start and span_id shouldn't be removed from the snapshots).

Add request forwarding for telemetry (#123)

This PR adds two middlewares to the Test-Agent. The first middleware stores the request data and headers in Test-Agent memory. The second middleware forwards requests to an optional end destination (such as a real DD Agent) for any requests from the /traces, /stats, or /telemetry endpoints.

Co-authored-by: Kyle Verhoog <kyle@verhoog.ca>

Add pipeline stats endpoint (#126)

Pool trace check failures and add endpoint to get failures (#124)

This PR adds functionality for pooling CheckTrace failures in-memory within the Test-Agent. Functionality was also added to query the Test-Agent for these failures. If they occurred, the Agent will send a bad response with the failures as the message body. The PR also adds the following environment variables:

DD_POOL_TRACE_CHECK_FAILURES: When set to true, the Test-Agent will pool trace check failures in memory. Can also be set using the --pool-trace-check-failures command line option.
DD_DISABLE_ERROR_RESPONSES: When set to true, the Test-Agent will disable error responses when a trace check failure occurs. Can also be set using the --disable-error-responses command line option.
